    "summary": "Total Rewards within multinationals, mid-size and/or scale up organisations. \n\nPROFILE\n\nCreative, result-driven and ambitious total rewards and performance professional. \n\nStrategic thinker and with eye-for-detail.\n\nPassion for sustainability, transformation and innovation. Committed and no nonsense. \n\nHands on. Focusses on people's strengths and capabilities.\n\nHigh analytical intelligence and friendly assertive personality\n\nSeasoned in Human Resources and HR operations.\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nIntroduced and implemented change -, transition - and improvement programs with global brands, scale ups and fast-growing entities, including Agilyx, GrandVision, Liberty Global, Nestl\u00e9, TomTom, Interxion and PWC.\n\nHuman Resources Management, Reward, Compensation & Benefits, Employee Recognition, Performance Management, Employee Happiness, HR Consulting and HR Marketing. \n\nMember of HR and executive management teams.\n\nExperienced and energized by working on middle to long term change projects in sustainable, dynamic and demanding environments.\n\nHands-on, result-driven and creative in solutions.  Promotes simple, clear and accessible programs linked to business strategy.\n\nBroad and in-depth knowledge of human resources management, compensation & benefits, performance management, HR change management, executive pay, tax, legal, M&A, financial reporting and HR operation.\n\nIntroduced, revisited and managed procurement of benefits programs (amongst others, pension, car policies, expense policies, health).\n\nMaster of Laws (tax) and Certified Global Remuneration Professional (WorldatWork Society of Certified Professionals).\n\nTrustworthy and strategic partner for senior managers and executives.\n\nBuilt and managed professional teams.",
